HEADWORD: Matricaria
<hw>Matricaria</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of chiefly Old
World strong-smelling weedy herbs; it comprises plants sometimes
included in other genera, such as <gen>Tanacetum</gen> and
<gen>Tripleurospermum</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Matricaria</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
